@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Submit Return Request (UC22)

autonumber
actor Customer
participant "Frontend View\n(JS / Browser)" as View
participant "ReturnRequestController\n(API Controller)" as Controller
participant "ReturnRequestService\n(Service)" as Service
participant "OrderRepository\n(Repo)" as OrderRepo
participant "ReturnRequestRepository\n(Repo)" as ReturnRepo
participant "OrderItemRepository\n(Repo)" as ItemRepo
database "MySQL\n(Database)" as DB

== Fetch My Orders with Return Info ==

Customer -> View : Open "My Orders" tab
View -> Controller : getReturnRequestsByCustomer()
note right: GET /api/return-requests
Controller -> Service : getReturnRequestsByCustomer(userId)
Service -> ReturnRepo : findByCustomerId(userId)
ReturnRepo -> DB : SELECT * FROM return_requests WHERE user_id = ?
DB --> ReturnRepo : List<ReturnRequest>
ReturnRepo --> Service : entities
Service --> Controller : List<ReturnRequestResponseDTO>
Controller --> View : 200 OK (List<DTO>)

== Submit Return Request via API ==

Customer -> View : Fill info, upload images and click "Submit Return"
View -> Controller : submitReturnRequest(SubmitReturnRequestDTO)
note right: POST /api/return-requests (JSON via Fetch)
Controller -> Service : submitReturnRequest(dto)

group Validate Eligibility
    Service -> OrderRepo : findById(dto.getOrderId())
    OrderRepo --> Service : orderEntity
    
    Service -> Service : validate order ownership & status
    
    loop for each itemId
        Service -> Service : validate itemId exists in Order
        Service -> ReturnRepo : existsByOrderItemIdIn([itemId])
        ReturnRepo --> Service : boolean
        alt if already requested
            Service --> Controller : throw RuntimeException
            Controller --> View : 400 Bad Request
            View --> Customer : Display Error Message
        end
    end
end

group Save Return Request (Transaction)
    Service -> Service : create ReturnRequest entity\nstatus = PENDING_APPROVAL
    Service -> ReturnRepo : save(returnRequest)
    ReturnRepo -> DB : INSERT INTO return_requests...
    DB --> ReturnRepo : success
    
    loop for each itemId
        Service -> ItemRepo : update refund_status = RETURN_REQUESTED
        ItemRepo -> DB : UPDATE order_items
    end
end

Service --> Controller : ReturnRequest entity
Controller --> View : 200 OK (ReturnRequest)
View --> Customer : Refresh UI & Show Active Return Request

@enduml